prevSentence: This paper describes the results of the first shared task on generation of teacher responses in educational dialogues.
currentSentence: The goal of the task was to benchmark the ability of generative language models to act as AI teachers, replying to a student in a teacher-student dialogue.
maskedSentence: The goal of the task was to benchmark the ability of [MASK] to act as AI teachers, replying to a student in a teacher-student dialogue.
nextSentence: Eight teams participated in the competition hosted on CodaLab and experimented with a wide variety of state-of-the-art models, including Alpaca, Bloom, DialoGPT, DistilGPT-2, Flan-T5, GPT- 2, GPT-3, GPT-4, LLaMA, OPT-2.7B, and T5- base.

prevSentence: Shared Task on Generating AI Teacher Responses in Educational Dialogues.
currentSentence: The task aims to assess the performance of state-of-the-art generative models as AI teachers in producing suitable responses within a student-teacher dialogue.
maskedSentence: The task aims to assess the performance of state-of-the-art [MASK] as AI teachers in producing suitable responses within a student-teacher dialogue.
nextSentence: Our system comprises evaluating various baseline models using OpenAI GPT-3 and designing diverse prompts to prompt the OpenAI models for teacher response generation.

prevSentence: We believe that the presented taxonomy, benchmark, and human-annotated labels will streamline the evaluation process and help track the progress in AI tutors’ development.
currentSentence: In this paper, we investigate whether current state-of-the-art large language models (LLMs) are effective as AI tutors and whether they demonstrate pedagogical abilities necessary for good AI tutoring in educational dialogues.
